description:
The best-selling Sony franchise finally becomes an action-packed comic!

With Dr. Nefarious defeated and the universe safe, galactic heroes Ratchet and Clank return to the Solana galaxy for some well-earned rest and relaxation. But when entire planets begin disappearing from the universe without a trace, Galactic President Qwark calls them back into action to solve the mystery. As the rest of the universe erupts in panic, the duo must embark on an epic adventure that will pit them against their most capable adversary to date: a Markazian planet thief named Artemis Zogg!
name: Ears of War

description: In the Kaya province, there are two ways to rise in power - by controlling dragons or by slaying them. Seur-Chong, a hunter with the Dragon's Curse, took the latter path, but he doesn't care about power. He's just in the dragon slaying business for the money. With his partner, the gifted shaman Myung-Ho, he's quickly made a name for himself as a mercenary. Perhaps too big a name, as a rival dragon-hunting group, the Chunjoo, is now out to eliminate the duo. In order to keep off the Chunjoo's hitlist, Seur-Chong and Myung-Ho will have to join their payroll.
name: You Call Yourself Dragon Hunters?

description: After the Daechang-Nim and Ru-Ahn flee Kaya, Seur-Chong goes after the head of the local Chunjoo gang to seek revenge for what happened to Myung-Ho. The plot thickens when someone from Seur-Chong's past shows up - is he friend or foe? But first, in order to save Myung-Ho's life, Seur-Chong must decide whether or not to give him dragon's blood. Although it was dragon's blood that gave Seur-Chong his mighty abilities, it also gave him a curse that is slowly but surely turning him to stone. Drinking dragon's blood can grant one incredible power...but it can also kill you!
name: Vol. 2

description: Seur-Chong's violent past as well as the consequences of his recent actions against the Chunjoo catch up to him. His old foe Tae-Rang kidnaps Aranseur - Myung-Ho's younger sister - in and attempt to exact revenge on the dragon hunter and his shaman sidekick for something they did to him in their youth. When Myung-Ho and Seur-Chong track down the kidnapper they come face to face with an Imogi monster serpent. Bitter adversaries must then join forces against not one, but two common enemies when another assassin joins the fray!
name: Vol. 3

description: Now in the kingdom of Shi-La, dragon hunter Seur-Chong and shaman Myung-Ho seek out the guardian dragon of the Dragon God in order to rid themselves of a curse. However, they are sidetracked by a desperate woman named Sun-Hwa. She too is a shaman but one who possesses a magic flute that she uses as a powerful weapon and a means to control dragons. With a shady Japanese military faction after the flute, Sun-Hwa enlists the dragon hunters to protect her and the dragon she controls. This leads to an adventure at sea and a prelude to a rematch between Seur-Chong and the Daechang-Nim!
name: Vol. 4

description: Seur-Chong is an elite dragon hunter. His partner, Myung-Ho, is a shaman who uses magic to control dragons. Together, they are a formidable dragon hunting team...and they're fighting to protect what would normally be their prey! A devastating battle ensues in which alliances are changed, trusts are betrayed, and loyalties are tested. In the end, it won't be a question of who has won...but who has lost the most!
name: Vol. 5

description: Now working as a shaman for the prime minister of the country of Ko-Gu-Ryo, Myung-Ho's sister Aranseur sets out to recruit Seur-Chong to hunt the Blue Dragon of Mount Back-Doo. Meanwhile, Seur-Chong encounters a powerful new dragon hunter named Goong-Chun and his shaman sidekick Sa-Mi. But will this chance meeting end in a new rivalry or mark the beginning of a new alliance? Big secrets about Seur-Chong's past are revealed, including the tragic fate of his mother, his history with the dubious Daechang-Nim, and other mysteries all relating to the deadly Blue Dragon of Mount Back-Doo.
name: Vol. 6

description: Seur-Chong and the gang finally arrive at Mount Back-Doo, home of the Blue Dragon and the last place Seur Chong saw his mother. But the plot thickens when Daechang-Nim of the Killer Clan, a second team of dragon hunters, and two opposing armies show up at the mountain. The tension mounts, the battle comes to a dramatic head, and shocking secrets are revealed about Seur-Chong's mother's connection to the Shamanic Council as well as who his father is.
name: Vol. 7

description: With the Daemackleejee's forces now entrenched within the Blue Dragon's realm and going on the offensive, the Chinese army makes one last desperate move to turn the tide. Meanwhile, Seur-Chong, Myung-Ho, and the others frantically struggle to escape from Mount Bak-Do, trapped between the angry Blue Dragon and the two battling armies. And in the midst of all this chaos, the deadly assassin Ru-Ahn's past is revealed, the Daechang-Nim of the Killer Clan is injured, a mother and son are finally reunited...but for how long?
name: Vol. 8

description: After failing to capture the Blue Dragon, Seur-Chong and his followers flee Mount Bak-Do to the safety of the country of Kaya. Once there, a mysterious female knight flying on a hotheaded dragon promises to inflict revenge on Tae-Rang. Seur-Chong doesn't understand what's going on, but one thing's for sure--he is caught in the middle of yet another dragon-related drama!
name: Vol. 9

description:
Fame, honor, and respect come with knighthood--but at what cost? Kok-Jung has been requested by Merlin to accompany him on a dragon hunt to capture Siegfried's Dragon. Merlin has some dark secrets and ulterior motives that only Beul-Hee knows about...but will she get the chance to tell Kok-Jung? Also, what exactly is the Wiseman's Stone and what power does it hold? Only Merlin knows, but his lips are sealed...

Back Blurb

Fame, honor, and respect come with knighthood but -- for a Korean knight in King Arthur's court -- mystery, intrigue, and betrayal are also part of the job.

Things seem simple enough when Merlin asks Kok-Jung to help capture Siegfriend's dragon... but Kok-Jung's shaman Beul-Hee knows Merlin has dark secret and ulterior motives. Can Beul-Hee warn Kok-Jung in time? If she can't, will the headstrong, young dragon hunter survive a battle with an enraged army of Camelot's knights?

Chapter Titles

  • Chapter 55: The West (Part 3): Acceptance
  • Chapter 56: The West (Part 4): Merlin's Secrets
  • Chapter 57: The West (Part 5)
  • Chapter 58: The West (Part 6): Merlin's Ulterior Motive
  • Chapter 59: The West (Part 7): Siegfried's Dragon
  • Chapter 60: The West (Part 8): The Philosopher's Stone
  • Chapter 61: The West (Part 9): Riah's Excalibur
  • Chapter 62: The West (Part 10): Controlling Siegfried's Dragon
  • Chapter 63: The West (Part 11): Tae-Rang's Fury (Part 1)
  • Chapter 64: The West (Part 12): Tae-Rang's Fury (Part 2)

(Note - For some reason all chapters in this volume are listed as chapter 55)
name: Vol. 10

description: After discovering out Merlin's true colors, Kok-Jung is on a quest for revenge, and he'll destroy Merlin's most precious commodity... The Philosopher's Stone! After breaking the stone, Kok-Jung is faced with having Siegfried's Dragon hot on his tail all the way back to his homeland. Can Seur-Chong and the others control the dragon's wrath and bring forth the demise of Merlin?
name: Vol. 11

description: This is beginning of the end! As the epic tale of "The West" wraps up, the final chapter of the Dragon Hunter saga, "The Chunjoo," begins. The Chunjoo is an enigmatic group of dragon hunters...but who staretd this criminal organization and what does the Chunjoo do with the countless dragons they've slain?
name: Vol. 12

description: While Seur-Chun and Ru-Ahn fight for their very lives, many terrible secrets are revealed! In a flashback to Seur-Chun's youth, we see how a hunt for a lightning dragon forced Seur-Chun to make a terrible choice...and how his decision forever altered his life and the lives of his wife and son! Back in the present, Seur-Chong must decide whether or not to aid Seur-Chun's fight for survival...but even if the young Dragon Hunter wants to help his estranged father, how can he fight when his powerful sword is in pieces?
name: Vol. 13

description: Seur-Chong and Myung-Ho are in Shi-La to destroy the Chunjoo once and for all. At the same time, Goong-Chun is trying to escape from the clutches of the Chunjoo. But Chong-Kwan-Jang sends his deadly dragon powered bodyguards after all three of them. Mong-Yeun discovers two shocking things about her past. The plot thickens when a mysterious assassin with a hungry dragon in tow attacks So-Chun and the Shamanic Council in Kaya where Sa-Mi is in hiding.
name: Vol. 14

description: Seur-Chong and Myung-Ho reunite with Goong-Chun at the Chunjoo's headquarters. Myung-Ho attempts to avenge his sister's death when he encounters Goong-Chun...but vengeance will have to wait: the two suddenly come face to face with a vicious dragon!
name: Vol. 15

description: Choo-Ryung has Sa-Mi in his clutches and Goon-Chun is her last chance at salvation. Meanwhile, Seur-Chong and the rest of the gang are tied-up with Chong-Kwan-Jang's most dangerous bodyguard. The Philosopher Stone may be the hunters only weapon to defeat the horrible Choo-Ryung. More drama unfolds once secrets connecting Sa-Mi and Mong-Yeun are revealed to our fair-weather heroes.
name: Vol. 16

description: As Chong-Kwan-Jang's secrets are revealed, Seur-Chong and his gang try to stop him... Is his power even greater than anyone realizes? Meanwhile, an attempted rescue of Mong-Yeun and Sa-Mi--who are under Chong-Kwan-Jang's spell--not only leads Myung-Ho to the past, but into their very minds!
name: Vol. 17

description: A year has passed since Myung-Ho ventured into the past to learn more about Mong-Yeun and Sa-Mi. Posing as Goong-Chun, he discovers his enemy has the curse of the Dragon God. Meanwhile Chong-Kwan-Jang prepares to hunt a dragon that keeps attacking the fishermen of Woosan Kingdom. As he gets ready, he comes across the Dragon God himself, a meeting that will change the course of his life for ever!
name: Vol. 18

description: Gleam had always been careful to hide her magical abilities, but when her brother is injured in a fight she has no choice but to use her powers to save him in public. That draws the attention of the templars, and one knight in particular: Duty, who was once known as Sadatt—her father. Will this reunion bring joy or death to both?
name: Might vs Magic

description: The Joes battle Mother Nature as a tidal wave threatens to sweep Scarlett, Ripcord and their strike team off an abandoned COBRA atoll. At the same time, Shipwreck, Cover Girl and the others have captured a COBRA weapon of mass destruction. But can they hold onto it? Action, mayhem, and post-nuclear consequences on the high seas!

The vigilante back from the dead versus the villain who can't seem to die! The man called Atrocity is in police custody, but finding out who is under the mask is only the beginning of the mystery. The true motive behind the killing is revealed and it leads to the moment that ShadowHawk fans have been waiting for since he reclaimed the helmet.
name: Resurrection, Part Four

description: Golden Age comic series

Joseph Burrows is your average type of guy - whose life is tuned upside down when he is witness to a murder - a digital murder. A visit from a virtual "ghost" reveals that life is not what we expect it to be. Could it be one big lie... or is it the start to unraveling the secret to the world we live in?

Joseph and Gerry have found a way to crack the code and start to experiment with their findings - creating something that will change both of their lives forever. A security camera video tape reveals that Joseph is a suspect to a murder and the police are on the hunt for him as well as the Hackers who are known for their non tolerant manner.
